<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: Arda is my module for ToME 3, still in development, that attempts to make a better ToME. <p>
I'm re-writing the monsters list from scratch to make a steadier power rise while staying in-theme.  Trolls should be scary, Balrogs should be awesome, and Dragons should be about the most powerful monsters in the game.  Almost everything on the side of Morgoth should be evil and/or corrupted. 
</p>
<p>
I'm re-writing the items list from scratch for many reasons.  I want to eliminate junk, make a more-interesting weapons list (to take pity on the poor <a class="interwiki" title="Self" href="./Classes/Axemaster">Axemasters</a>), make artifacts rarer and more useful, and re-do the ego list. 
</p>
<p>
I'm expanding the map and adding many more towns. 
</p>
<p>
The game has a long way to go, though.  With everything else I do for ToME (like setting up this wiki), Arda keeps getting put off. 
</p>
<p>
The latest Arda sources are available in my <a class="external" href=".www.gnu.org/software/gnu-arch/">GNU Arch</a> archive <tt>neil@hakubi.us--terminus</tt> in branch <tt>arda--mainline</tt>.  <tt>neil@hakubi.us--terminus</tt> is available at <tt>http://www.hakubi.us/arch/terminus/</tt> 
</p>
<hr size="3">
 <p>
There is some discussion of the module at <a href="./GeneralDiscussion_2fArda_20musings">GeneralDiscussion/Arda musings</a> 
</p>
